      structure A :
      sig
	structure B : sig end;
      end;
      sharing A = A.B;
    end;

Comment: NJML accepts the above signature declaration, which should be
         rejected because it elaborates to a cyclic semantic object;
         cyclic objects are not semantically admissible.

